</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unelmunbar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nelmunbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/19/01 1:33:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Reason why WE are not gonna go FFA.</span><hr size=1> Some people here have openly expressed interest in FFA.  Llanos is in favor of it.  Qualtar kinda says he wants it, or at least thinks he'll benefit from it somehow.  While these people's opinions may not represent the overall views of their guilds (ET and BI respectively), the supporters for it are there.<br>
<br>
I personally think that if FFA did erupt, these people would be kicking themselves for ever supporting it in the first place.  But I cannot predict the future or pretend to know others' reactions to unknown events.  So that's just an opinion of mine.<br>
<br>
I think a FFA situation would eventually cool down and become more self moderated, with the major guilds coming to some pseudo agreement on how to share things.  But that's basically how this scheduling system started in the first place.  <br>
<br>
I try to avoid analogies, but a FFA would be similar to a war.  The fighting would only last a short while probably.  But it's the aftermath that scares me.  The destruction of everything the Brell community has worked so had to build and maintain.  Not just the scheduling systems, but the trust that the larger guilds have in each other.  Sure, some members have differences with each other, but generally most guilds on this server are more than willing to help another guild if the need arises.  All of that would go up in smoke if the war happens.  We'd be starting from scratch.<br>
<br>
<br>
