50 Enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uqualtarshylok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qualtar Shylok</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/19/01 4:11:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/blood_inferno/images/QualtarShylok.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Reason why WE are not gonna go FFA.</span><hr size=1> Well, the problem with stating FFA is people are scared of it... This server has actually given a bad name to it equating it to such things as KS'n... which I am not in favor of.<br>
<br>
As dear friend of mine (Jondin) wrote on the BI message board, one of the best times of his ever was a day when he logged online and had no idea what his plans were that day, he ended up killing a dragon by the end of the day and expressed it was the funnest thing he had ever done in game.<br>
<br>
Thats what I favor... the ability to log on and head anywhere you want without the worry of soanso guild has that mob &quot;reserved&quot; as you stand there staring at it.  The game was not designed like that, and we deprive all of ourselves good gaming opportunities because of these rules.<br>
<br>
Everyone talks about how great each other is on the server, but they obviously don't trust each other as far as they can see or we wouldn't have these rules.  (I am sure that paragraph will get quoted and flamed a few times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
