<br>
Fair enough.  I can see the distinction between the two.  I kinda think that FFA would lead to kill stealing, but it does not necessarily have to, if all the parties involved have a mutual respect for each other.  And that mutual respect would probably take the form of in-game communications, as you pointed out:<br>
<br>
&quot;Instead of having reservation list, we could have &quot;killed&quot; list...&quot;<br>
<br>
But don't you think this would lead to a general system of things?  As more guilds get added, and more people want to do the same thing, communication and organization of everyone involved would get much more complex to handle in-game.  So what would be the problem with taking those communications to an outside source that is more appropriate to handle it...such as these boards?  Then you're back to where we are now.<br>
<br>
It just seems that Brell, as a whole (please remember that part), prefers a lawful order to the sharing of mobs on our server.  Does this take some of the spontaneity out of the game?  Yes, of course, which is kinda sad.  And I'm all for logical ideas on how to improve that, without risking the benefits of what these boards have created; a place where anyone can get a shot at almost anything.<br>
<br>
I hope I have fully understood your points as well as you've understood mine.  If I have misunderstood something you've said, or took it out of context, then please correct me.  I would like this to stay civil and not degenerate into flames, because I'm not mad at anyone here.  And I hope you don't get mad at me.  I'm just trying to discuss.<br>
